"We have contact," Shaw shouted into the radio as orange tracer rounds were fired from the crest. Bullets ricocheted off the sides of the tanks, while soldiers leaped from the vehicles to take cover behind them. A anti-tank missile whistled past and exploded behind the formation, sending debris flying and striking one of the vehicles. Another anti-tank missile struck the side of an M109A6 Stryker, an APS-Cerberus, and detonated. Its crew scrambled out and dove for cover as the ammunition inside ignited.
