"Shall we kill them or capture them?" asked Craith as they watched them.
"It seems they were captured," Cohren stepped forward as the two Sentinels disappeared in a cloud of ashes and smoke. Shouts and gunfire echoed from the ridge, but ceased quickly. A moment later, the two Sentinels returned, dragging someone behind them, whose boots dragged on the ground. Once safely with the squad, they dropped the individual to the ground. He groaned in pain as he collapsed in the mud and snow.
Shaw walked towards the individual, who was beginning to rise. He turned towards one of the Sentinels. "How many?"
"Three dead, sir," replied the Sentinel. "The others fled on foot."
Shaw nodded and turned towards Cohren and Craith, who were standing beside him. "Would both of you have the kindness to get rid of this man for us?"
